#  SOP 01 – Month-End Close

## Overview
This Standard Operating Procedure governs the execution of the
month-end close to ensure financial information is accurate,
complete, timely, and fully supportable.

The SOP establishes a controlled and repeatable framework
for preparing, reviewing, and approving close activities.

## Key Areas
• Roles and responsibilities  
• Close workflow and task lifecycle  
• Status and RAG monitoring  
• Evidence and documentation requirements  
• Estimates and exception handling  
• Dependency management  
• Post-close adjustment governance  
• Version control and approvals  

## Close Framework
• Locked master template  
• Controlled working files  
• Assumption tracking  
• Evidence hierarchy  
• Structured sign-off  

## Control Philosophy
• No task is complete without evidence  
• Independent review is mandatory  
• Changes after preparation require visibility  
• Risk and materiality drive escalation  

## Timeline
The standard close cycle typically spans approximately
ten working days, depending on complexity.

## Standards
IFRS – Fair Presentation & Accrual Accounting  
IAS 1 – Presentation of Financial Statements  

